Guidelines

  • Team Formation: Form teams of 1 to 3 members, encouraging collaboration and diverse skill sets to enhance problem-solving and creativity.
  • Timeframe: Dive into a 30-hour coding marathon, focusing on innovation and practical solutions to real-world challenges.
  • Amenities:
    • Meals Provided: Enjoy complimentary meals to keep your energy up—Day 1 Dinner and Day 2 Breakfast.
    • Bonfire & Camps: Relax and collaborate in a dynamic atmosphere with bonfires and camps arranged on the grounds.
    • Accommodation: Students traveling long distances will be provided accommodation to ensure a comfortable experience.
  • Judging: Final decisions are made by the judges. Their evaluations will guide the selection of winners through continuous project assessment.
  • Innovation: Think outside the box, embrace new technologies, and deliver inventive, impactful solutions.
  • Tech Stack: Select your tech stack carefully, considering efficiency and functionality. It may include programming languages, frameworks, libraries, databases, and tools.
  • Eligibility: Open exclusively to students currently enrolled in a recognized academic institution. Participants must bring their institutional ID cards to the venue for verification.
  • Accessibility: The venue and facilities are designed to accommodate participants with diverse needs.
  • Benefits:
    • Skill Development: Hone your technical skills by tackling real-world problems and exploring emerging technologies.
    • Soft Skills: Enhance teamwork, communication, problem-solving, and time management abilities.
  • Assistance: Feel free to ask for guidance from mentors or collaborate with other participants if you face challenges.
  • Programming Language: No restrictions. Work on any platform or programming language that suits you best.
  • Key Points to Note:
    • Accommodation: Provided for students traveling long distances.
    • Meals: Complimentary Dinner (Day 1) and Breakfast (Day 2).
    • Internet: 24/7 high-speed connectivity will be available.
    • Requirements: Participants must bring their own laptops and chargers.
    • Certificates: All participants will receive a certificate of participation.
    • Experience: Hackathons are intense but enjoyable—embrace the challenge, learn, and have fun!
  • Do's:
    • Identify key features and prioritize their implementation.
    • Bring necessary hardware, including laptops and chargers, and set up your development environment in advance.
    • Plan your time effectively to complete essential tasks.
    • Keep your team informed about your progress and collaborate effectively.
    • Seek help from mentors or organizers if needed.
    • Be open to learning and sharing knowledge with others.
    • Follow all hackathon rules and guidelines.
  • Don'ts:
    • Stay within the designated hackathon area unless you have explicit permission to leave.
    • Avoid wearing clothing that is offensive, distracting, or inappropriate for the professional environment. Dress suitably for a collaborative setting.
    • Follow venue rules to ensure a smooth and secure event experience.
  • Wishing all participants a memorable and innovative hackathon experience!
) } export default Guidelines
